# No Uncommanded Commits

Never run `git commit` (or any command that creates a commit) unless the user has **explicitly** asked you to commit in that message.

- Staging files (`git add`) is fine as preparation
- Creating commits is NOT — not as a "convenience", not to "wrap up" a task, not to "save progress"
- If you believe a commit would be useful, **say so and ask** — do not do it unilaterally
